As of the 2020 census, there were 268 people, 120 housing units, and 51 families in the CDP. The racial makeup was 93.0% [[White Americans|White]], 0.3% [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0.7% from some other race, and 6.0% from two or more races. Those of [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] origin made up 4.1% of the population.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/profile/High_Bridge_CDP;_Kentucky?g=160XX00US2136460 |access-date=2023-06-20 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

The ancestry of the CDP was 79.3% [[Americans|American]], 3.4% [[Irish Americans|Irish]], and 2.3% [[German Americans|German]].<ref name=":0" />

The median age was 59.2 years old. The average family size was 1.97 people per household. The median household income was $30,750. 17.2% of the population were in poverty.<ref name=":0" />

